Author::::Mathew Porter
DateTime::::2016-03-11T14:06:46Z
I'm co-cordinator of the Learner Development Special Interest Group of the Japan Association for Language Teaching and an Assistant Professor of English. My group worked with a small group of English students across Japan to translate reflections written one year after 3.11 by junior high school students who survived the disaster. Amazingly, although their school was only a few meters from the sea everyone managed to evacuate in time, although most lost their houses and some lost family members. Their reflections often recount the gratitude and bonds that helped them overcome tragedy. We produced a web page to share some of the reflections, which can be found at http://lookingback311.wix.com/start



