Author::::Mark Richards
DateTime::::2016-03-11T12:48:21Z
As was my custom I had NHK (Japan's BBC equivalent - only less corrupt) running in the background as I worked late into the evening (east coast, US). The earthquake detection and alerting system in Japan is so efficient that the warning flashed upon the screen before the first tremor was felt, with the Tsunami alert following. I watched, in horror, live images from the coastline, Tokyo downtown, and eventually the Fukushima plant. No sleep, but tears, and a desire to be there and do something to help filled my heart.



