Author::::yokoso
DateTime::::2016-03-11T08:42:50Z
Tokyo didn't really get much damage. My biggest hardship was a 4 hour walk home, but it was heartwarming to see folks cooperating. Apartment buildings with notices inviting those in need to use their toilets, etc. My wife brought 3 complete strangers home from shopping & we fed them and lent a bicycle to one - which was duly returned the next day with a box of cookies as a thank you. Nobody fighting for a taxi on my route- anyway traffic was totally gridlocked & walking was faster.



