Author::::akiksmt
DateTime::::2016-03-11T05:10:09Z
I was more devastated by the nuclear accident than the quake and tsunami, I am afraid I had to say, and my immediate thought was how my parents might have felt when they realized the defeat at the end of WWII. (What I learned later was feeling like this was not uncommon among people of my generation, baby boomers.) I knew our system was flawed but not this flawed; I thought it was at least better than the Soviet Union which brought about the Chernobyl. Betrayed I found myself cursing Japan, all those people saying "This is a natural disaster beyond our imagination, so no one's responsible. Now fortified (within our restrained imagination), we can bring back the nuclear plants."



