Author::::Jason Gomez
DateTime::::2016-03-11T03:27:19Z
I was in Yokohama preparing to pick the kids up from school at 3pm when it hit. Many people dont know but there was a foreshock 2 days before, that Wednesday, at almost exactly the same time. This made me think the Friday earthquake was similar, until about a minute in. It was like the washing machine switched to spin cycle at about 1 minute in. That really scared me since that was the time the Wed. quake actually finished. This one, instead, upped in intensity by multiple factors. The building went from swaying side to side to jumping up and down.



Author::::Skytree
DateTime::::2016-03-11T03:23:58Z
Yes. To me the great surprise was stepping out from our building afterwards into a beautiful spring afternoon and seeing someone clutching a freshly-bought starbucks. I couldn't believe that life could look so normal.



